WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:02.742
[ Music playing ]

00:21.021 --> 00:22.853
[vocalizing ends]

02:15.761 --> 02:17.752
[sizzling ]

02:55.634 --> 02:57.625
<i>[ Narrator reading ]</i>

03:40.637 --> 03:43.004
DJINN: Make your second wish.

04:12.961 --> 04:14.747
[ Screams ]

04:19.468 --> 04:20.708
[ Screams ]

04:27.809 --> 04:29.846
[creature laughing ]

04:33.565 --> 04:35.602
[ Screams ]

04:43.909 --> 04:46.571
Help me, Sorcerer! Help me!

04:56.880 --> 04:58.496
[gurgling]

05:04.221 --> 05:06.929
[gurgling continues]

05:14.147 --> 05:16.058
[screaming ]

05:17.400 --> 05:18.435
No.

05:23.114 --> 05:25.105
[overlapping chatter]

05:34.167 --> 05:35.373
Free us, wizard.

05:37.671 --> 05:39.253
Help ussss!

05:42.843 --> 05:44.834
[ Hissing ]

05:46.680 --> 05:48.136
MAN: No!

06:06.908 --> 06:08.569
No more wishes, please.

06:47.449 --> 06:49.440
[growling]

06:53.330 --> 06:56.493
DJINNI Yes.

06:59.127 --> 07:00.117
[ Gasps ]

07:01.129 --> 07:02.619
[ Groans ]

07:04.132 --> 07:07.124
[speaking incantation ]

07:13.642 --> 07:14.973
No.

07:16.561 --> 07:21.772
[echoing ] No!

07:37.916 --> 07:39.907
- [overlapping chatter]
- [seabirds calling ]

07:45.507 --> 07:48.465
[ Bell rings]

07:58.561 --> 08:01.053
MAN: I'm surprised you're here
in person, Mr. Beaumont.

08:21.126 --> 08:23.743
It's a miracle
this one was ever made.

08:34.431 --> 08:35.466
[thump]

08:51.698 --> 08:53.655
[ Screams ]

08:54.993 --> 08:56.279
[ Groans ]

09:00.331 --> 09:02.618
10 years...

09:04.586 --> 09:06.372
All right, come on. Move it!
Let's go, everybody!

09:21.895 --> 09:23.852
Shit. He's gone.

09:54.219 --> 09:56.005
Hi. Can I help you?

10:22.705 --> 10:25.413
Wow, this is--This--

10:51.192 --> 10:53.980
<i>♪ Yeah, I could second-guess I'</i>

11:06.624 --> 11:09.992
Well, how is, um, Rick?

11:23.766 --> 11:26.679
Well, I thought maybe we...

11:27.979 --> 11:28.969
What?

11:52.754 --> 11:54.916
Wait. You know what it is?
I'm just...

11:56.424 --> 11:57.914
I'm just worried about losing

12:02.513 --> 12:04.345
How 'bout dinner and a movie?

12:12.106 --> 12:14.017
I'm going out on a limb here.

12:19.197 --> 12:21.529
I'm casting a spell
on you here, Alex.

12:23.201 --> 12:24.987
Maybe it'll work.

12:30.667 --> 12:31.702
Hey.

12:35.505 --> 12:37.416
I'll see you later.

12:41.302 --> 12:43.043
Think about what I said.

12:45.974 --> 12:47.715
[radio playing rock-'n'-roll ]

13:04.951 --> 13:07.033
My God.

13:11.916 --> 13:14.032
How magnificent?

13:15.336 --> 13:18.249
- Excellent translucence.
- Mm-hmm.

13:22.885 --> 13:24.751
It's unique.

13:40.028 --> 13:41.143
- Nick.
- Hmm?

13:54.876 --> 13:56.287
Hmm.

13:57.628 --> 13:59.460
What's this?

14:06.554 --> 14:09.216
[ Exhales ]

14:18.816 --> 14:22.025
DJINN: You woke me.

14:30.870 --> 14:35.785
<i>You woke me.</i>

14:56.396 --> 14:57.636
0h, my God!

15:07.615 --> 15:08.855
I think...

15:10.076 --> 15:12.067
there may be
something wrong with it.

15:22.672 --> 15:24.288
GIRL: Oh, hi!

15:27.885 --> 15:29.876
[overlapping chatter]

15:35.518 --> 15:37.304
There's something inside of it?

15:40.106 --> 15:42.393
I don't know. I'm no gemologist.

15:43.734 --> 15:45.975
I could run
some spectral analysis,

16:19.103 --> 16:20.093
[girls groan]

16:59.143 --> 17:00.759
Shoot the ball.

17:07.693 --> 17:09.479
Okay.

17:13.324 --> 17:16.406
<i>COMPUTER: Laser targeting,
full analysis.</i>

17:25.711 --> 17:28.328
Well, this is the easiest date
you've ever gotten, Aickman.

17:36.806 --> 17:38.388
What is that?

17:42.228 --> 17:45.971
DJINN: You woke me.

17:50.987 --> 17:52.398
[alarm beeping ]

18:00.746 --> 18:02.282
[Djinn laughs]

18:12.758 --> 18:14.749
[dialing]

18:16.679 --> 18:19.341
[telephone line ringing ]

18:22.435 --> 18:23.971
[telephone rings]

18:31.902 --> 18:34.360
[ring]

18:36.866 --> 18:39.858
[ring]

19:07.980 --> 19:09.766
Yes.

19:13.027 --> 19:15.018
Oh, God.

19:17.365 --> 19:19.697
[coughing]

19:25.831 --> 19:27.822
<i>There's no place
where you can call me back.</i>

19:38.010 --> 19:41.298
I can ease your suffering.

19:42.807 --> 19:45.970
All you have to do is ask.

19:57.780 --> 19:59.487
As you wish.

20:05.496 --> 20:06.702
[ Gasps ]

20:13.796 --> 20:14.786
Josh!

20:20.553 --> 20:23.170
Oh, my God.

20:26.434 --> 20:27.924
Josh!

20:36.902 --> 20:38.893
[growling]

20:42.199 --> 20:44.315
Oh, my God.

20:52.543 --> 20:54.910
[ Exhales ]

21:19.278 --> 21:21.269
[siren blaring ]

21:28.579 --> 21:30.320
[camera clicks]

21:36.337 --> 21:38.453
Right in that spot, right there.

21:52.394 --> 21:54.726
Miss, I'm sorry.

21:59.193 --> 22:00.979
Alex Amberson.

22:02.488 --> 22:06.152
Alex Amberson, eh? Good.

22:10.704 --> 22:13.162
He was my best friend.

22:14.792 --> 22:17.204
L-I'm sorry.

22:22.842 --> 22:24.549
It looks like an accident,

22:28.430 --> 22:30.216
You have any idea
what he was working on?

22:31.475 --> 22:33.933
He was analyzing...

22:35.354 --> 22:38.517
a gemstone, opal.

22:39.984 --> 22:41.315
It was for me.

22:50.202 --> 22:51.442
Excuse me, lady.

23:08.512 --> 23:10.094
Look, how many times
I gotta tell you?

23:17.521 --> 23:19.808
Well, you don't tell me
how to run my life.

23:47.176 --> 23:51.044
Discomplected afterbirth
of a Chinese gangbanger!

23:52.056 --> 23:53.967
Educated idiot!

24:07.237 --> 24:08.978
I hope you rot in hell!

24:19.041 --> 24:20.406
Tell me...

24:23.128 --> 24:27.213
do you really mean
those curses you hurl so freely?

24:28.342 --> 24:30.253
You're damn right, I did.

24:35.349 --> 24:36.589
Cigarette and a handshake

25:01.875 --> 25:03.786
Give it some thought.

25:09.550 --> 25:11.882
Eh, he should only get cancer.

25:16.015 --> 25:19.178
Should only get cancer and die.

25:28.193 --> 25:29.183
Hey, buddy, you okay?

25:30.154 --> 25:31.360
[ Gasps ]

25:37.953 --> 25:39.569
- You okay?
- I don't know.

25:52.593 --> 25:53.833
[ Gasps ]

26:02.478 --> 26:04.936
Was it worth it?

26:06.315 --> 26:08.932
[gasping ]

26:11.779 --> 26:13.986
[screaming ]

26:16.408 --> 26:18.570
Run, insect.

26:35.469 --> 26:36.504
[continues screaming ]

27:02.579 --> 27:05.788
Hey. You're not enjoying it.

27:12.923 --> 27:16.837
Hey, Alex,
I'm really sorry about Josh.

27:22.850 --> 27:24.807
No, we weren't as close
as he wanted,

27:33.569 --> 27:35.401
I think it is.

27:41.410 --> 27:46.155
There was something weird
in the opal.

27:47.666 --> 27:49.828
I think that was what exploded.

27:51.170 --> 27:53.878
I think what I gave Josh
is what killed him.

28:06.268 --> 28:08.134
[Sighs]

28:17.571 --> 28:19.061
I'm fine.

28:20.240 --> 28:21.856
I'm just upset.

28:31.084 --> 28:32.745
Why don't you go to bed?

29:07.246 --> 29:09.157
It's nothing like last time.

29:13.210 --> 29:14.951
But something's going on...

29:17.297 --> 29:18.958
something bad.

29:22.511 --> 29:24.969
I'm gonna find out what it is.

29:35.107 --> 29:37.098
[woman screaming ]

29:38.986 --> 29:42.604
Help! Help! Alex!

29:52.791 --> 29:54.156
[fading 1
<i>Help.</i>

30:04.303 --> 30:05.384
Ready to play, Alex?

30:12.978 --> 30:16.767
<i>DAMN: I can smell your fear.</i>

30:28.201 --> 30:31.114
I'm looking for a dockworker
named Etchison.

30:41.089 --> 30:43.126
Mr. Etchison?

30:55.562 --> 30:57.223
The jewel?

31:12.704 --> 31:16.242
All right. What's the deal?
You a cop?

31:23.423 --> 31:26.506
Out of that statue
after the accident.

31:38.313 --> 31:40.850
Hey, Clegg gave me
a couple hundred.

31:43.110 --> 31:44.396
Royally.

31:46.822 --> 31:48.813
[overlapping chatter]

31:58.041 --> 32:00.578
MAN: Hey. Fuck.

32:29.239 --> 32:31.651
[ Piano music playing ]

32:38.290 --> 32:40.156
Alexandra.

32:50.760 --> 32:54.344
Mr. Beaumont, I'm so sorry
about what happened.

32:59.936 --> 33:01.722
We are talking about Ed Finney,

33:46.358 --> 33:48.895
[ Man whistles a tune]

33:53.406 --> 33:55.272
- [ Man yells]
- Jesus!

34:15.094 --> 34:16.505
Wow.

34:28.775 --> 34:30.641
See that? Down there,

34:38.577 --> 34:41.114
It's the objects
I collect, Alex,

34:49.545 --> 34:51.708
So he was a god of good, then?

34:53.757 --> 34:55.623
Interestingly, though,

35:07.689 --> 35:09.305
There's someone
at the university

35:22.871 --> 35:24.657
[ Man whistling a tune]

35:27.667 --> 35:29.203
[ Scoffs ]

35:43.725 --> 35:45.807
What the fuck?!

36:15.048 --> 36:17.039
Aah! My eyes!

36:20.178 --> 36:22.169
[wailing]

36:24.933 --> 36:25.923
MY eyes!

36:28.144 --> 36:29.555
[wails]

36:34.275 --> 36:35.857
Alex!

36:41.866 --> 36:43.948
Uh...

36:46.162 --> 36:48.153
[gasping ]

36:50.041 --> 36:53.750
Sorry.
I don't know what happened.

36:54.921 --> 36:56.457
You fainted.

37:05.432 --> 37:07.548
No, I'm fine.

37:11.312 --> 37:13.394
But I'm fine honestly.

37:33.251 --> 37:35.913
Well, thank you. I'd like to.

37:36.963 --> 37:39.295
But I think I may be busy.

37:40.925 --> 37:42.256
Hmm.

37:44.095 --> 37:45.711
- Little more!
- That's it!

38:25.261 --> 38:27.093
- Uh-huh. What can I do for you?
- All right?

38:32.227 --> 38:34.138
I like you.

38:47.492 --> 38:49.074
The Stone of the Secret Fire

39:28.950 --> 39:30.566
You tell me.

39:38.668 --> 39:41.000
[sighs] Wow.

39:45.133 --> 39:47.374
Um, do you want
to try something else?

39:55.977 --> 39:58.719
Okay, then. Follow me.

40:07.280 --> 40:10.693
<i>♪ It's easy to say I'</i>

40:15.246 --> 40:18.079
Now, will this be
cash or charge, Mr...

40:28.593 --> 40:29.754
[laughs]

40:33.640 --> 40:34.846
Oh.

40:38.102 --> 40:42.221
This is my first day
in your world, Ariella.

40:57.914 --> 41:00.281
Well, I--| mean,

41:19.435 --> 41:22.678
L--l wish
to be beautiful forever.

41:31.698 --> 41:33.985
<i>♪ Well, I love you, babe... l'</i>

41:36.744 --> 41:39.611
<i>DAMN: Soon I will find you.</i>

41:45.003 --> 41:46.243
No.

41:59.809 --> 42:01.140
Thanks.

42:03.312 --> 42:04.552
You all right?

42:05.565 --> 42:06.976
Yes.

42:47.482 --> 42:48.972
In the old writings,

43:06.667 --> 43:07.657
OFFICER: Hmm.

43:31.192 --> 43:32.728
Case is closed,

43:58.553 --> 44:00.464
Why do you
keep looking over there?

44:03.099 --> 44:04.134
Guilty as sin.

44:12.942 --> 44:14.808
Just once,
I'd like it to be easy.

44:23.452 --> 44:25.159
[ Groans ]

44:28.374 --> 44:30.661
[ People screaming ]

44:39.969 --> 44:42.051
- Hold him down!
- [ gun firing]

44:45.600 --> 44:46.681
- Hold him!
- [gun clatters]

44:51.689 --> 44:53.555
We need them cuffs on him.

44:58.946 --> 45:00.653
Hey, you!

45:13.085 --> 45:14.792
[ Screams ]

45:16.422 --> 45:18.038
[yelling]

45:20.843 --> 45:22.834
[gunfire continues]

45:28.059 --> 45:30.676
[gasping ]

45:46.452 --> 45:48.819
<i>"The Stone of the Secret Fire,</i>

46:35.376 --> 46:37.367
Sorry, sir, we're closed.

46:40.256 --> 46:41.667
There's no one here,
just the boss.

46:55.938 --> 46:58.100
Okay, pal.
It's time for you to go.

47:00.901 --> 47:02.357
Get out of my way.

47:03.404 --> 47:04.610
I don't think so, asshole.

47:06.282 --> 47:08.239
Do you have any idea
how frustrating it is

47:25.926 --> 47:28.793
No. No.

47:50.159 --> 47:52.150
[screaming ]

47:54.747 --> 47:56.363
[screaming continues]

48:09.553 --> 48:11.715
Who the hell are you?
How'd you get in here?

48:12.890 --> 48:14.506
Guard opened up for me.

48:15.643 --> 48:17.680
I wonder
if I could ask your help.

48:20.689 --> 48:22.976
I'm looking
for Alexandra Amberson.

49:05.901 --> 49:07.892
Hey, hey!
That's a very valuable piece!

49:09.613 --> 49:14.608
Really? Would you like it
to be 100 times as valuable?

49:29.175 --> 49:30.586
Holy shit.

49:32.928 --> 49:35.340
How'd you--What are you,
David Copperfield or something?

49:58.287 --> 50:01.279
Well, I'm not a greedy man.

50:04.668 --> 50:06.158
Done.

50:22.686 --> 50:23.926
There you go.

50:31.320 --> 50:32.310
SHANNON: Hey.

50:33.364 --> 50:35.856
Hey, yourself.

50:49.171 --> 50:51.788
Damn. I lost track of time.

50:56.720 --> 50:58.085
[Sighs]

51:01.225 --> 51:03.808
- [overlapping chatter]
- Over here! I'm open!

51:07.982 --> 51:09.017
Good job! Yay!

51:16.532 --> 51:18.398
Stillness, Ms. Amberson,

51:24.582 --> 51:25.572
WOMAN: Go, girls!

51:38.554 --> 51:39.715
<i>This is Wendy Derleth.</i>

51:51.984 --> 51:53.349
Thank you.

51:54.695 --> 51:56.402
- Come on!
- Throw!

52:18.218 --> 52:19.174
<i>This is Wendy Derleth.</i>

52:29.480 --> 52:31.517
Useful little items,
aren't they?

52:34.860 --> 52:36.851
[ Chatter continues ]

52:47.206 --> 52:48.742
- Go for three!
- Got it!

53:05.599 --> 53:07.590
[chimes tinkling]

53:12.606 --> 53:14.597
[clock clicks, chiming ]

53:44.388 --> 53:46.004
[ Growls ]

53:52.938 --> 53:54.599
[ring]

54:07.453 --> 54:10.036
There was a guy here
looking for you.

54:12.833 --> 54:14.369
[gasping ]

54:23.761 --> 54:27.504
<i>'</i> [gasps]
<i>'</i> [groaning]

54:30.267 --> 54:32.178
[ Gasps ]

54:35.981 --> 54:38.894
[wailing]

54:45.699 --> 54:47.235
[ Exhales ]

54:54.333 --> 54:57.746
[Djinn laughs]

55:08.430 --> 55:10.421
[panfing]

55:16.355 --> 55:18.346
[ Phone beeping rapidly]

55:25.531 --> 55:26.692
<i>,</i> [telephone rings]
<i>'</i> Yelps!

55:28.325 --> 55:29.406
[ring]

55:30.702 --> 55:32.284
Hello.

55:46.260 --> 55:49.628
Patience, friends.

55:58.313 --> 56:00.099
[ Knocking on door]

56:08.198 --> 56:10.610
Hi. Um, can I come in?

56:16.957 --> 56:18.539
Stone is charged.

56:34.016 --> 56:36.132
No. Uh, thank you.

56:38.729 --> 56:41.346
This is a nice cabinet,
isn't it?

56:47.362 --> 56:49.069
You didn't?

56:52.367 --> 56:53.949
Then how would I know?

56:54.995 --> 56:57.157
Maybe Beaumont mentioned it.

57:03.045 --> 57:05.082
Let me explain.

57:16.141 --> 57:18.428
It certainly existed.

58:22.749 --> 58:24.990
I'm not hungry.
I'm not thirsty. I'm not--

58:32.843 --> 58:34.754
[laughs]

58:39.099 --> 58:40.260
I'm sorry.

58:41.351 --> 58:43.217
I guess I'm just a little tense.

58:49.651 --> 58:50.891
I guess.

58:52.696 --> 58:54.278
But I'm fine.

58:57.159 --> 58:58.524
Where were we?

58:59.536 --> 59:00.526
Oh, yes.

59:01.538 --> 59:04.872
No spells, no hope.

59:10.338 --> 59:12.375
I'll have to rely on myself.

59:56.551 --> 59:57.882
I must be going now.

59:58.929 --> 01:00:00.920
[chimes tinkling]

01:00:01.598 --> 01:00:03.339
DJINNI Sit down.

01:00:06.186 --> 01:00:09.304
Please sit down.

01:00:14.236 --> 01:00:16.443
- Where's Wendy?
- Bedroom,

01:00:52.482 --> 01:00:55.600
You're a dangerous person
to know, Alexandra.

01:00:56.611 --> 01:00:58.318
Your scientist friend,

01:01:02.409 --> 01:01:03.865
By the by,

01:01:09.916 --> 01:01:14.501
If you harm Shannon,
I'll kill you.

01:01:33.481 --> 01:01:36.644
Three wishes, Alexandra.

01:01:42.032 --> 01:01:43.488
Anything you want.

01:02:20.570 --> 01:02:23.312
<i>'</i> [ Gasps]
<i>'</i> [ sighs]

01:02:24.866 --> 01:02:28.530
That which is eternal
cannot die.

01:02:42.425 --> 01:02:45.417
I always tell my girls
to know their opponent...

01:02:51.393 --> 01:02:56.388
so I think I will make a wish.

01:03:01.987 --> 01:03:04.354
To know what you are.

01:03:07.784 --> 01:03:09.616
What are you doing?

01:03:15.250 --> 01:03:17.537
[souls wailing]

01:03:21.631 --> 01:03:23.713
[ Growls ]

01:03:25.635 --> 01:03:28.718
You wished to know what I am.

01:03:57.250 --> 01:03:59.116
[creature growling ]

01:04:06.384 --> 01:04:07.749
[speaking foreign language]

01:04:11.222 --> 01:04:12.508
Oh, shit.

01:04:36.373 --> 01:04:37.784
WOMAN: Alex!

01:04:39.876 --> 01:04:42.459
[ Distant voices whispering ]

01:04:52.514 --> 01:04:54.221
<i>_</i> [ Djinn sighs]
<i>'</i> [ gasps]

01:04:58.895 --> 01:05:02.763
So how do you like me so far?

01:05:27.132 --> 01:05:29.089
- [ Gasps 1
- Oh, Alexandra,

01:05:52.115 --> 01:05:55.699
Stop me then.
Wish yourself back.

01:06:06.212 --> 01:06:07.202
[wailing stops 1

01:06:09.090 --> 01:06:10.421
Shannon?

01:06:11.634 --> 01:06:13.375
Shannon, where are you?

01:06:19.184 --> 01:06:20.219
Damn it.

01:06:27.066 --> 01:06:28.682
[telephone rings]

01:06:40.914 --> 01:06:42.450
FUCK you!

01:06:44.584 --> 01:06:46.541
[tires squealing ]

01:06:51.633 --> 01:06:53.920
[car horn honks]

01:06:59.265 --> 01:07:00.255
[car horn honks]

01:07:02.644 --> 01:07:05.227
- [tires squeal ]
- [ men yell ]

01:07:08.816 --> 01:07:09.806
[ Screams ]

01:07:41.432 --> 01:07:43.423
[thunder crashing ]

01:07:44.769 --> 01:07:45.850
Excuse me, ma'am.

01:08:03.955 --> 01:08:06.037
Excuse me, sir.

01:08:09.794 --> 01:08:12.377
I asked you a question, sir.

01:08:13.381 --> 01:08:16.169
Am I expected? Yes.

01:09:48.643 --> 01:09:49.758
Yeah.

01:09:50.853 --> 01:09:52.514
As you wish.

01:09:54.315 --> 01:09:58.775
[groaning]

01:10:10.039 --> 01:10:12.030
[ Light overlapping chatter]

01:10:17.004 --> 01:10:18.415
- [woman yelps]
- ALEX: Excuse me.

01:10:20.258 --> 01:10:21.589
Excuse me.

01:10:23.886 --> 01:10:25.126
MAN: Yes, please.

01:10:27.557 --> 01:10:28.843
- Excuse me.
